{"paragraphs":[{"cues":[{"time":471,"text":"The great texts of the ancient world"},{"time":2955,"text":"don't survive to us in their original form."},{"time":6270,"text":"They survive because medieval scribes copied them"},{"time":9789,"text":"and copied them and copied them."},{"time":11788,"text":"And so it is with Archimedes,"},{"time":14438,"text":"the great Greek mathematician."}]},{"cues":[{"time":16204,"text":"Everything we know about Archimedes as a mathematician"},{"time":19206,"text":"we know about because of just three books,"},{"time":21904,"text":"and they're called A, B and C."},{"time":23820,"text":"And A was lost by an Italian humanist in 1564."},{"time":28653,"text":"And B was last heard of in the Pope's Library"},{"time":31456,"text":"about a hundred miles north of Rome in Viterbo in 1311."},{"time":37288,"text":"Now Codex C was only discovered in 1906,"},{"time":41585,"text":"and it landed on my desk in Baltimore"},{"time":44134,"text":"on the 19th of January, 1999."},{"time":48260,"text":"And this is Codex C here."}]},{"cues":[{"time":50678,"text":"Now Codex C is actually buried in this book."},{"time":55847,"text":"It's buried treasure."},{"time":57297,"text":"Because this book is actually a prayer book."},{"time":59632,"text":"It was finished by a guy called Johannes Myrones"},{"time":62596,"text":"on the 14th of April, 1229."},{"time":66213,"text":"And to make his prayer book he used parchment."},{"time":68698,"text":"But he didn't use new parchment,"},{"time":71113,"text":"he used parchment recycled from earlier manuscripts,"},{"time":74427,"text":"and there were seven of them."},{"time":76164,"text":"And Archimedes Codex C was just one of those seven."},{"time":79647,"text":"He took apart the Archimedes manuscript and the other seven manuscripts."},{"time":85114,"text":"He erased all of their texts,"},{"time":88497,"text":"and then he cut the sheets down in the middle,"},{"time":90915,"text":"he shuffled them up,"},{"time":93159,"text":"and he rotated them 90 degrees,"},{"time":95077,"text":"and he wrote prayers on top of these books."},{"time":97129,"text":"And essentially these seven manuscripts"},{"time":98826,"text":"disappeared for 700 years, and we have a prayer book."}]},{"cues":[{"time":103174,"text":"The prayer book was discovered by this guy,"},{"time":106423,"text":"Johan Ludvig Heiberg, in 1906."},{"time":109150,"text":"And with just a magnifying glass,"},{"time":110591,"text":"he transcribed as much of the text as he could."},{"time":113475,"text":"And the thing is that he found two texts in this manuscript"},{"time":116657,"text":"that were unique texts."},{"time":118425,"text":"They weren't in A and B at all;"},{"time":120025,"text":"they were completely new texts by Archimedes,"},{"time":121723,"text":"and they were called \"The Method\" and \"The Stomachion.\""},{"time":124958,"text":"And it became a world famous manuscript."}]},{"cues":[{"time":127227,"text":"Now it should be clear by now"},{"time":129042,"text":"that this book is in bad condition."},{"time":131756,"text":"It got in worse condition in the 20th century"},{"time":135226,"text":"after Heiberg saw it."},{"time":136958,"text":"Forgeries were painted over it,"},{"time":138475,"text":"and it suffered very badly from mold."},{"time":141558,"text":"This book is the definition of a write-off."},{"time":145308,"text":"It's the sort of book"},{"time":147042,"text":"that you thought would be in an institution."},{"time":149707,"text":"But it's not in an institution,"},{"time":151893,"text":"it was bought by a private owner in 1998."}]},{"cues":[{"time":156525,"text":"Why did he buy this book?"},{"time":158275,"text":"Because he wanted to make that which was fragile safe."},{"time":161812,"text":"He wanted to make that which was unique ubiquitous."},{"time":165058,"text":"He wanted to make that which was expensive free."},{"time":169724,"text":"And he wanted to do this as a matter of principle."},{"time":172859,"text":"Because not many people are really going to read Archimedes in ancient Greek,"},{"time":177391,"text":"but they should have the chance to do it."}]},{"cues":[{"time":180075,"text":"So he gathered around himself the friends of Archimedes,"},{"time":183374,"text":"and he promised to pay for all the work."},{"time":185510,"text":"And it was an expensive job,"},{"time":187208,"text":"but actually it wouldn't be as much as you think"},{"time":190678,"text":"because these people, they didn't come from money,"},{"time":192843,"text":"they came from Archimedes."},{"time":194662,"text":"And they came from all sorts of different backgrounds."},{"time":196378,"text":"They came from particle physics,"},{"time":198561,"text":"they came from classical philology,"},{"time":200127,"text":"they came from book conservation,"},{"time":202095,"text":"they came from ancient mathematics,"},{"time":204677,"text":"they came from data management,"},{"time":206594,"text":"they came from scientific imaging and program management."},{"time":209511,"text":"And they got together to work on this manuscript."}]},{"cues":[{"time":213067,"text":"The first problem was a conservation problem."},{"time":216878,"text":"And this is the sort of thing that we had to deal with:"},{"time":219311,"text":"There was glue on the spine of the book."},{"time":221511,"text":"And if you look at this photograph carefully,"},{"time":223712,"text":"the bottom half of this is rather brown."},{"time":225760,"text":"And that glue is hide glue."},{"time":227128,"text":"Now if you're a conservator,"},{"time":228513,"text":"you can take off this glue reasonably easily."},{"time":230645,"text":"The top half is Elmer's wood glue."},{"time":234010,"text":"It's polyvinyl acetate emulsion"},{"time":236127,"text":"that doesn't dissolve in water once it's dry."},{"time":238794,"text":"And it's much tougher than the parchment that it was written on."},{"time":241960,"text":"And so before we could start imaging Archimedes,"},{"time":245311,"text":"we had to take this book apart."},{"time":246760,"text":"So it took four years to take apart."},{"time":249611,"text":"And this is a rare action shot, ladies and gentlemen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":253144,"text":"(Laughter)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":255915,"text":"Another thing is that we had to get rid of all the wax,"},{"time":260181,"text":"because this was used in the liturgical services"},{"time":262416,"text":"of the Greek Orthodox Church"},{"time":264157,"text":"and they'd used candle wax."},{"time":265468,"text":"And the candle wax was dirty,"},{"time":267331,"text":"and we couldn't image through the wax."},{"time":268564,"text":"So very carefully we had to mechanically scrape off all the wax."}]},{"cues":[{"time":271899,"text":"It's hard to tell you exactly"},{"time":273801,"text":"how bad this condition of this book is,"},{"time":276515,"text":"but it came out in little bits very often."},{"time":279281,"text":"And normally in a book, you wouldn't worry about the little bits,"},{"time":281631,"text":"but these little bits might contain unique Archimedes text."},{"time":284631,"text":"So, tiny fragments"},{"time":286930,"text":"we actually managed to put back in the right place."}]},{"cues":[{"time":291671,"text":"Then, having done that, we started to image the manuscript."},{"time":295381,"text":"And we imaged the manuscript"},{"time":296881,"text":"in 14 different wavebands of light."},{"time":298909,"text":"Because if you look at something in different wavebands of light,"},{"time":302815,"text":"you see different things."},{"time":304031,"text":"And here is an image of a page"},{"time":305598,"text":"imaged in 14 different wavebands of light."}]},{"cues":[{"time":308115,"text":"But none of them worked."},{"time":310248,"text":"So what we did was we processed the images together,"},{"time":314665,"text":"and we put two images into one blank screen."},{"time":317965,"text":"And here are two different images of the Archimedes manuscript."},{"time":320798,"text":"And the image on the left"},{"time":322614,"text":"is the normal red image."},{"time":323965,"text":"And the image on the right is an ultraviolet image."},{"time":325877,"text":"And in the image on the right"},{"time":327017,"text":"you might be able to see some of the Archimedes writing."},{"time":329465,"text":"If you merge them together into one digital canvas,"},{"time":332447,"text":"the parchment is bright in both images"},{"time":335265,"text":"and it comes out bright."},{"time":337140,"text":"The prayer book is dark in both images"},{"time":340156,"text":"and it comes out dark."},{"time":341853,"text":"The Archimedes text is dark in one image and bright in another."},{"time":345204,"text":"And it'll come out dark but red,"},{"time":347604,"text":"and then you can start to read it rather clearly."},{"time":349871,"text":"And that's what it looks like."}]},{"cues":[{"time":352713,"text":"Now that's a before and after image,"},{"time":356055,"text":"but you don't read the image on the screen like that."},{"time":359037,"text":"You zoom in and you zoom in"},{"time":361656,"text":"and you zoom in and you zoom in,"},{"time":365204,"text":"and you can just read it now."}]},{"cues":[{"time":367272,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":373620,"text":"If you process the same two images in a different way,"},{"time":377200,"text":"you can actually get rid of the prayer book text."},{"time":379770,"text":"And this is terribly important,"},{"time":380788,"text":"because the diagrams in the manuscript"},{"time":383771,"text":"are the unique source for the diagrams"},{"time":386238,"text":"that Archimedes drew in the sand in the fourth century B.C."},{"time":389055,"text":"And there we are, I can give them to you."}]},{"cues":[{"time":392094,"text":"With this kind of imaging --"},{"time":394438,"text":"this kind of infrared, ultraviolet, invisible light imaging --"},{"time":397104,"text":"we were never going to image through the gold ground forgeries."},{"time":399704,"text":"How were we going to do that?"},{"time":401557,"text":"Well we took the manuscript,"},{"time":403520,"text":"and we decided to image it in X-ray fluorescence imaging."},{"time":407807,"text":"So an X-ray comes in in the diagram on the left"},{"time":410821,"text":"and it knocks out an electron from the inner shell of an atom."},{"time":414673,"text":"And that electron disappears."},{"time":416671,"text":"And as it disappears, an electron from a shell farther out"},{"time":420306,"text":"jumps in and takes its place."},{"time":422788,"text":"And when it takes its place,"},{"time":424221,"text":"it sheds electromagnetic radiation."},{"time":427055,"text":"It sheds an X-ray."},{"time":428487,"text":"And this X-ray is specific in its wavelength"},{"time":431138,"text":"to the atom that it hits."}]},{"cues":[{"time":433020,"text":"And what we wanted to get"},{"time":435188,"text":"was the iron."},{"time":436921,"text":"Because the ink was written in iron."},{"time":438788,"text":"And if we can map"},{"time":440471,"text":"where this X-ray that comes out, where it comes from,"},{"time":443055,"text":"we can map all the iron on the page,"},{"time":445121,"text":"then theoretically we can read the image."}]},{"cues":[{"time":447720,"text":"The thing is that you need a very powerful light source to do this."},{"time":452055,"text":"So we took it to the Stanford Synchrotron Radiation Laboratory"},{"time":455429,"text":"in California,"},{"time":456871,"text":"which is a particle accelerator."},{"time":458439,"text":"Electrons go around one way,"},{"time":460171,"text":"positrons go around the other."},{"time":461788,"text":"They meet in the middle,"},{"time":463104,"text":"and they create subatomic particles"},{"time":465540,"text":"like the charm quark and the tau lepton."},{"time":467770,"text":"Now we weren't actually going to put Archimedes in that beam."},{"time":470792,"text":"But as the electrons go round at the speed of light,"},{"time":474340,"text":"they shed X-rays."},{"time":475607,"text":"And this is the most powerful light source in the solar system."},{"time":478257,"text":"This is called synchrotron radiation,"},{"time":480206,"text":"and it's normally used to look at things"},{"time":482024,"text":"like proteins and that sort of thing."},{"time":483691,"text":"But we wanted it to look at atoms, at iron atoms,"},{"time":487688,"text":"so that we could read the page from before and after."},{"time":490557,"text":"And lo and behold, we found that we could do it."},{"time":492855,"text":"It took about 17 minutes to do a single page."}]},{"cues":[{"time":496303,"text":"So what did we discover?"},{"time":498958,"text":"Well one of the unique texts in Archimedes"},{"time":501140,"text":"is called \"The Stomachion.\""},{"time":502943,"text":"And this didn't exist in Codices A and B."},{"time":505357,"text":"And we knew that it involved this square."},{"time":507776,"text":"And this is a perfect square,"},{"time":509569,"text":"and it's divided into 14 bits."},{"time":511590,"text":"But no one knew what Archimedes was doing with these 14 bits."},{"time":514373,"text":"And now we think we know."},{"time":516557,"text":"He was trying to work out"},{"time":518324,"text":"how many ways you can recombine those 14 bits"},{"time":520857,"text":"and still make a perfect square."},{"time":523184,"text":"Anyone want to guess the answer?"},{"time":526686,"text":"It's 17,152 divided into 536 families."},{"time":532048,"text":"And the important point about this"},{"time":534415,"text":"is that it's the earliest study in combinatorics in mathematics."},{"time":538129,"text":"And combinatorics is a wonderful and interesting branch of mathematics."}]},{"cues":[{"time":541893,"text":"The really astonishing thing though about this manuscript"},{"time":545128,"text":"is that we looked at the other manuscripts"},{"time":547497,"text":"that the palimpsester had made,"},{"time":548915,"text":"the scribe had made his book out of,"},{"time":551481,"text":"and one of them was a manuscript containing text by Hyperides."},{"time":554413,"text":"Now Hyperides was an Athenian orator from the fourth century B.C."},{"time":558781,"text":"He was an exact contemporary of Demosthenes."},{"time":561198,"text":"And in 338 B.C. he and Demosthenes together"},{"time":565597,"text":"decided that they wanted to stand up"},{"time":567281,"text":"to the military might of Philip of Macedon."},{"time":569281,"text":"So Athens and Thebes went out to fight Philip of Macedon."},{"time":572930,"text":"This was a bad idea,"},{"time":574198,"text":"because Philip of Macedon had a son called Alexander the Great,"},{"time":577631,"text":"and they lost the battle of Chaeronea."}]},{"cues":[{"time":579914,"text":"Alexander the Great went on to conquer the known world;"},{"time":582632,"text":"Hyperides found himself on trial for treason."},{"time":585382,"text":"And this is the speech that he gave when he was on trial --"},{"time":588982,"text":"and it's a great speech:"},{"time":590130,"text":"\"Best of all,\" he says, \"is to win."},{"time":592398,"text":"But if you can't win,"},{"time":594132,"text":"then you should fight for a noble cause,"},{"time":596173,"text":"because then you'll be remembered."},{"time":597748,"text":"Consider the Spartans."},{"time":599346,"text":"They won enumerable victories,"},{"time":601214,"text":"but no one remembers what they are"},{"time":603046,"text":"because they were all fought for selfish ends."},{"time":605181,"text":"The one battle that the Spartans fought that everybody remembers"},{"time":608747,"text":"is the the battle of Thermopylae"},{"time":610463,"text":"where they were butchered to a man,"},{"time":612466,"text":"but fought for the freedom of Greece.\""},{"time":614398,"text":"It was such a great speech"},{"time":616663,"text":"that the Athenian law courts let him off."},{"time":620398,"text":"He lived for another 10 years,"},{"time":622464,"text":"then the Macedonian faction caught up with him."},{"time":625115,"text":"They cut out his tongue in mockery of his oratory,"},{"time":627699,"text":"and no one knows what they did with his body."},{"time":631130,"text":"So this is the discovery of a lost voice from antiquity,"},{"time":634281,"text":"speaking to us, not from the grave,"},{"time":636263,"text":"because his grave doesn't exist,"},{"time":637741,"text":"but from the Athenian law courts."}]},{"cues":[{"time":639514,"text":"Now I should say at this point"},{"time":641163,"text":"that normally when you're looking"},{"time":643930,"text":"at medieval manuscripts that have been scraped off,"},{"time":645926,"text":"you don't find unique texts."},{"time":647412,"text":"And to find two in one manuscript is really something."},{"time":650514,"text":"To find three is completely weird."},{"time":653731,"text":"And we found three."}]},{"cues":[{"time":655412,"text":"Aristotle's \"Categories\""},{"time":656678,"text":"is one of the foundational texts of Western philosophy."},{"time":659131,"text":"And we found a third century A.D. commentary on it,"},{"time":663547,"text":"possibly by Galen and probably by Porphyry."}]},{"cues":[{"time":666731,"text":"Now all this data that we collected,"},{"time":668929,"text":"all the images, all the raw images,"},{"time":671464,"text":"all the transcriptions that we made and that sort of thing"},{"time":673814,"text":"have been put online under a Creative Commons license"},{"time":677300,"text":"for anyone to use for any commercial purpose."}]},{"cues":[{"time":680214,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":686747,"text":"Why did the owner of the manuscript do this?"},{"time":690051,"text":"He did this because he understands data as well as books."},{"time":693797,"text":"Now the thing to do with books,"},{"time":695132,"text":"if you want to ensure their long-term utility,"},{"time":697263,"text":"is to hide them away in closets"},{"time":699479,"text":"and let very few people look at them."},{"time":701279,"text":"The thing to do with data, if you want it to survive,"},{"time":703698,"text":"is to let it out and have everybody have it"},{"time":706999,"text":"with as little control on that data as possible."},{"time":710098,"text":"And that's what he did."}]},{"cues":[{"time":711262,"text":"And institutions can learn from this."},{"time":714690,"text":"Because institutions at the moment"},{"time":717242,"text":"confine their data with copyright restrictions and that sort of thing."},{"time":720299,"text":"And if you want to look at medieval manuscripts on the Web,"},{"time":722491,"text":"at the moment you have to go to the National Library of Y's site"},{"time":725962,"text":"or the University Library of X's site,"},{"time":728630,"text":"which is about the most boring way"},{"time":730529,"text":"in which you can deal with digital data."},{"time":732306,"text":"What you want to do is to aggregate it all together."}]},{"cues":[{"time":735299,"text":"Because the Web of the ancient manuscripts of the future"},{"time":738396,"text":"isn't going to be built by institutions."},{"time":740682,"text":"It's going to be built by users,"},{"time":743790,"text":"by people who get this data together,"},{"time":745564,"text":"by people who want to aggregate all sorts of maps"},{"time":749099,"text":"from wherever they come from,"},{"time":750731,"text":"all sorts of medieval romances"},{"time":752531,"text":"from wherever they come from,"},{"time":754080,"text":"people who just want to curate their own glorious selection"},{"time":757863,"text":"of beautiful things."},{"time":759380,"text":"And that is the future of the Web."},{"time":760997,"text":"And it's an attractive and beautiful future,"},{"time":764180,"text":"if only we can make it happen."}]},{"cues":[{"time":765782,"text":"Now we at the Walters Art Museum have followed this example,"},{"time":768963,"text":"and we have put up all our manuscripts on the Web"},{"time":772313,"text":"for people to enjoy --"},{"time":773996,"text":"all the raw data, all the descriptions, all the metadata."},{"time":776580,"text":"under a Creative Commons license."},{"time":779463,"text":"Now the Walters Art Museum is a small museum"},{"time":780981,"text":"and it has beautiful manuscripts,"},{"time":782529,"text":"but the data is fantastic."},{"time":784547,"text":"And the result of this"},{"time":786330,"text":"is that if you do a Google search on images right now"},{"time":789348,"text":"and you type in \"Illuminated manuscript Koran\" for example,"},{"time":792680,"text":"24 of the 28 images you'll find come from my institution."}]},{"cues":[{"time":797097,"text":"(Applause)"}]},{"cues":[{"time":802647,"text":"Now, let's think about this for a minute."},{"time":807680,"text":"What's in it for the institution?"},{"time":809663,"text":"There are all sorts of things that are in it for the institution."},{"time":812259,"text":"You can talk about the Humanities and that sort of thing,"},{"time":814382,"text":"but let's talk about selfish things."},{"time":816263,"text":"Because what's really in it for the institution is this:"},{"time":820131,"text":"Now why do people go to the Louvre?"},{"time":823187,"text":"They go to see the Mona Lisa."},{"time":826171,"text":"Why do they go to see the Mona Lisa?"},{"time":829230,"text":"Because they already know what she looks like."},{"time":831612,"text":"And they know what she looks like"},{"time":833946,"text":"because they've seen pictures of her absolutely everywhere."}]},{"cues":[{"time":838648,"text":"Now, there is no need"},{"time":843097,"text":"for these restrictions at all."},{"time":845376,"text":"And I think that institutions should stand up"},{"time":847463,"text":"and release all their data under unrestricted licenses,"},{"time":850597,"text":"and it would be a great benefit to everybody."},{"time":852813,"text":"Why don't we just let everybody have access to this data"},{"time":855979,"text":"and curate their own collection"},{"time":858315,"text":"of ancient knowledge and wonderful and beautiful things"},{"time":860480,"text":"and increase the beauty and the cultural significance"},{"time":863568,"text":"of the Internet."}]},{"cues":[{"time":864796,"text":"Thank you very much indeed."}]},{"cues":[{"time":866313,"text":"(Applause)"}]}]}